<BLOCKQUOTE><i>
Though I of course would never recommend that anyone log out in a dungeon, I thought I'd drop by and forward a warning nonetheless. Rumor has it that some areas once considered "safe" will not be after tomorrow's patch. Please spread the word.<BR><BR>
-Gordon
</BLOCKQUOTE></i> 
			<br><br>
			
			
		
	
			<a name="199"></a>
			<FONT COLOR="4a0000"><B>Extremely Low Delay Weapons</B></FONT><BR>
			<TABLE border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1"><TR>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2"><a href="responses.cfm?id=199">Add Comment</A> (0)</font> &nbsp; &nbsp;</TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2"><a href="index.cfm?category_id=4" title="View news of this category"><font color="ca0000">Dev Quotes</font></a></font> &nbsp; &nbsp; </TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2">Server: N/A</font>&nbsp;</TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2">Posted By: <A HREF="mailto:dantes@eqrealms.com">Dantes</A></font> &nbsp; &nbsp; </TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2">02:44 PM</font>&nbsp;</TD>
			</TR></TABLE>
			Gordon "Abashi" Wrinn made a comment on the boards reguarding the extremely low delay weapons (moss covered twig and the barbed scale whip) and current plans to change them because they are unbalanced.<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE><i>
About a month ago I mentioned that we were still investigating the issue with some low delay weapons that entered the game recently, among these are the mosscovered twig and the barbed scale whip. 
<BR><BR>
After analyzing combat data concerning use of these weapons, it is apparent that a change must be made to maintain (or restore in this case) balance. While we have no problem with weapons of this delay, they should not have been placed as loot on anything other than deity or dragon level encounters. As it is, these weapons were dropping off of low to mid level encounters, leading to thousands of them in game. 
<BR><BR>
The next time we patch items, the extreme low-delay one-handed weapons (a list of specific items to follow in the near future) will be modified so that they can only be equipped in the off-hand. This will address the balance issue present with these items.
<BR><BR>
-Gordon
</i></BLOCKQUOTE>
By changing the weapons to offhand only, the player won't get the benefit of the mainhand 1H damage bonus. 
			<br><br>
			
			
		
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	</TD></TR>
	</TABLE>

