			<a name="196"></a>
			<FONT COLOR="4a0000"><B>More Changes for the Better</B></FONT><BR>
			<TABLE border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1"><TR>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2"><a href="responses.cfm?id=196">Add Comment</A> (0)</font> &nbsp; &nbsp;</TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2"><a href="index.cfm?category_id=1" title="View news of this category"><font color="ca0000">General</font></a></font> &nbsp; &nbsp; </TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2">Server: N/A</font>&nbsp;</TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2">Posted By: <A HREF="mailto:korie@eqrealms.com">Korie</A></font> &nbsp; &nbsp; </TD>
			<TD bgcolor="#aaaaaa"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="-2">07:07 PM</font>&nbsp;</TD>
			</TR></TABLE>
			Using emotes on NPCs will work again in the near future (not this patch, but the next). You'll be able to /laugh at the dancing skeleton in Paineel or /point at the Guk Ghoul Lord instead of haling him. We've also increased the range of socials, so you'll be able to do that stuff when they are further away.
<p>

He also tells me that /who all "guildname" will work for /roleplayers as well. I know you all have been asking for that one for a while. 
<p>
-Gordon 
			<br><br>
			
			
		
	
